			<div class="themedArea">
			<h1 id="it-is-not-">It is not:</h1>
<h2 id="a-web-framework">A web framework</h2>
<h2 id="a-programming-language">A programming language</h2>
<h1 id="it-wants-to-be-">It wants to be:</h1>
<h3 id="simple-and-relatively-easy-to-understand-and-use">Simple and relatively easy to understand and use</h3>
<h3 id="useful-for-i-o-based-programs-that-need-to-be-fast-and-or-handle-lots-of-connections">Useful for I/O based programs that need to be fast and/or handle lots of connections</h3>

			</div>
			
			</div>
		
		</div>
	
		
			<div style="position: absolute; transform: translate(-50%, -50%) translate3d(13926.4px, 2764.8px, 0px) rotateX(0deg) rotateY(0deg) rotateZ(0deg) scale(3); transform-style: preserve-3d;" id="step-4" class="step future" data-state="strut-slide-3" data-x="13926.4" data-y="2764.8" data-scale="3">
			<div class="bg-solid-smoke slideContainer strut-slide-3" style="width: 1024px; height: 768px;">
			<div class="themedArea">
			<h2 id="it-is-designed-to-be-good-at-">It is designed to be good at:</h2>
<ul>
<li>Building network programs using the protocols of the web: HTTP, TCP, UDP, DNS and SSL</li>
<li>Building programs that read and write data to the filesystem or local processes/memory<ul>
<li>Databases (e.g. MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Redis, CouchDB)</li>
<li>APIs (e.g. Twitter, Facebook, Apple Push Notifications)</li>
<li>HTTP/WebSocket connections (from users of a web app)</li>
<li>Files (image resizer, video editor, internet radio)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Using non-blocking, event-driven I/O to remain lightweight and 
efficient in the face of data-intensive real-time applications that run 
across distributed devices</li>
</ul>

			</div>
			
			</div>
		
		</div>
	
		
