			<div class="themedArea">
			<h1 id="shipping">Shipping</h1>
<ul>
<li>$ node app.js (in reality a service that starts the app)<ul>
<li>Clustered start of the app</li>
<li>Points to some port not exposed through FW</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Using Forever or Upstart or similar to keep running<ul>
<li>Because of bubbling exceptions</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Reverse proxy between instances and outside world<ul>
<li>Nginx &lt;3</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>(Maybe) load balancer between multiple configs mentioned above and outside world<ul>
<li>HAProxy</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>(Maybe) Deploy via git post-receive hooks (naturally)</li>
</ul>

